    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="col-right">
    <h1 class="section-tilte font-sans text-4xl card">About <span>us</span></h1>
    <section class="font-sans text-4xl card">
      <p class="font-sans text-4xl subpixel-antialiased">In 2014  , We dreamed of sharing healthy idli / Dosa batter .
         So we thought and started a company in Dindigal.
        We make idli and dosa batter for our Customers just the way they made it at home.
        Soon there were none left at the shelves because people loved our healthy preservative free Batter.
        We are making a high quality "Idli Dosa Batter" under very hygenic environment.<br>
        <br>
      We are using the best in class dhal and RO - purified water with no other preservatives or soda added.<br>
      <br>
    We are making this with great love and care , which suits for all ages from kids to adults.<br></p>

    <ul>
      <h4 class="text-4xl">How To Use ? </h4>
      <br>
      <h4>To Make Idli</h4>
      <br>
      <li>Open the pack and add salt if required. The Batter is mildly salted only.</li>
      <li>If you are making idli , directly scoop out the batter and pour it into the idli streamer.</li>
      <li>Stir the batter before pouring it into the moulds of the idli steamer for the soft idli.</li>
      <br>
      <h4>To Make Dosa</h4>
      <br>
      <li>If you are making dosa , add some water to dilute the batter.</li>
      <li>After dilution , the batter can no longer be used for making idli.</li>
    </ul>
    <br>
      <h4>How To Store ? </h4>
      <br>
      <ul>
        <li>Refrigerate at 0-5 degree . Bring the batter to room temperature before using it.</li>
      </ul>
      
    </section>
       
